</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8566145CE7C6FE10FE3E06A1" blockId="12.[151,1435,402,455]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE7C6FE10FED906CE" box="[151,263,403,424]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniurops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE7C6FE10FED906CE" box="[151,263,403,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Taeniurops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE6CDFE10FE2806CE" box="[412,502,403,424]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE6CDFE10FE2806CE" box="[412,502,403,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Taeniura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) Garman, 1913:399. 
<typeStatus id="54B5C5A98566145CE584FE10FCD906CE" box="[725,775,403,424]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE430FE10FB2306CE" authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1841" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1841" box="[865,1277,402,424]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meyeni">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE430FE10FBD206CE" box="[865,1036,403,424]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Taeniura meyeni</emphasis>
Müller &amp; Henle, 1841
</taxonomicName>
; by subsequent designation (Fowler, 1941).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31428808566145CE7C6FE70FB660412" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8566145CE7C6FE70FDA00436" blockId="12.[151,1437,499,1064]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE7C6FE70FED1056A" bold="true" box="[151,271,499,524]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Definition</emphasis>
. Large to very large dasyatids (adults to 
<quantity id="4CF6D6EE8566145CE5ADFE77FC55056A" box="[764,907,500,524]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" unit="cm" value="140.0" valueMax="180.0" valueMin="100.0">100–180 cm</quantity>
DW) characterised by the following: robust, almost circular disc; snout obtuse to broadly angular (2–2.2 times combined orbit and spiracle length); eye small and protruding slightly; nasal curtain broadly skirt-shaped; mouth medium-sized, with ~7 oral papillae (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE2D6FDBEFF38051E" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meyeni">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE2D6FDBEFF38051E" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">T. meyeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); tail firm and short (length slightly exceeding DW), its base rather broad and depressed; pelvic fins small, subrectangular, not protruding, inner margin long; dorsal fold absent; ventral fold deep with a long base; caudal sting positioned rather anteriorly on tail (distance from pectoral-fin insertion to caudal-sting base 2–2.3 times interspiracular width); skin rough in adults and denticle band absent; continuous strip of small median thorns on disc and tail in most adults, scapular thorns present or absent; tail prickly; strong dorsal colour plain or heavily black and white blotched; ventral disc white with dark margins; tail uniformly black; Atlantic (including the Mediterranean Sea) and Indo– 
<collectingRegion id="49CAB5E98566145CE6B8FCB4FDFC0436" box="[489,546,823,848]" country="Tanzania" name="Mjini Magharibi" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">West</collectingRegion>
Pacific.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8566145CE796FCD8FB660412" blockId="12.[151,1437,499,1064]" box="[199,1208,859,885]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE796FCD8FEC00412" bold="true" box="[199,286,859,884]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Species</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE67DFCDEFD230412" authority="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1817" authorityName="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1817" box="[300,765,860,885]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniurops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grabata">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE67DFCDEFE7E0413" box="[300,416,860,885]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">T. grabata</emphasis>
(Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1817)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE465FCDEFB6A0412" authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1841" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1841" box="[820,1204,860,885]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meyeni">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE465FCDEFC400412" box="[820,926,861,884]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">T. meyeni</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31428808566145CE796FC03FD75034E" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB17B0B8566145CE796FC03FD75034E" blockId="12.[151,1437,499,1064]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE796FC03FEEA04FE" bold="true" box="[199,308,896,920]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Remarks</emphasis>
. Formerly placed within 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE508FC02FD6504FE" box="[601,699,897,920]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE508FC02FD6504FE" box="[601,699,897,920]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Taeniura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F06FA8566145CE450FC03FC2204FE" author="Last" box="[769,1020,896,920]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" refString="Last, P. R. &amp; Stevens, J. D. (1994) Sharks and rays of Australia. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, 513 pp." type="book" year="1994">Last &amp; Stevens, 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F06FA8566145CE35BFC03FAF904FE" author="Last" box="[1034,1319,896,920]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" refString="Last, P. R. &amp; Compagno, L. J. V. (1999) Dasyatidae. In: Carpenter, K. E. &amp; Niem, V. H. (Eds.), Species identification guide for fisheries purposes. The living marine resources of the western central Pacific. Batoid fishes, chimeras and bony fishes part 1 (Elopidae to Linophrynidae). FAO, Rome, pp. 1479 - 1505." type="book chapter" year="1999">Last &amp; Compagno, 1999</bibRefCitation>
) and later resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9F06FA8566145CE66EFC26FD9F04DA" author="Last" box="[319,577,932,956]" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" refString="Last, P. R. &amp; Stevens, J. D. (2009) Sharks and rays of Australia, Second edition. CSIRO Publishing, Melbourne, 656 pp." type="book" year="2009">Last &amp; Stevens (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE51FFC26FD6604DA" box="[590,696,933,956]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="meyeni">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE51FFC26FD6604DA" box="[590,696,933,956]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">T. meyeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a monophyletic group with its cognate 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE396FC26FAE204DB" box="[1223,1340,932,957]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniurops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grabata">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE396FC26FAE204DB" box="[1223,1340,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">T. grabata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, outside the subfamily Neotrygoninae and within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE5DBFC44FCD70486" box="[650,777,967,992]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dasyatinae">Dasyatinae</taxonomicName>
, close to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE420FC4AFC0A0486" box="[881,980,969,992]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE420FC4AFC0A0486" box="[881,980,969,992]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<figureCitation id="1335678E8566145CE35CFC44FB930486" box="[1037,1101,967,992]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dasyatidae (subfamily Dasyatinae). Topology and branch lengths resulting from a constrained Maximum Likelihood analysis of aligned NADH 2 sequence data using the GTR + I + G model. Topological constraints were derived from an unpublished ML analysis of whole mitochondrial genomes for a representative subset of the taxa (unpublished). Members of the Neotrygoninae were used as outgroups. Names shown at branch tips are those currently in use. Revised generic names proposed are shown to the right." pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The two 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE399FC4AFA9C0486" box="[1224,1346,969,992]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Taeniurops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97AA7198566145CE399FC4AFA9C0486" box="[1224,1346,969,992]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Taeniurops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are morphologically distinct from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C0E00888566145CE507FC6FFD0D0363" box="[598,723,1004,1029]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dasyatinae">Dasyatinae</taxonomicName>
in disc shape (almost circular) and ventral tail fold morphology (fold unusually deep and continuous to tail tip).
</paragraph>
